# CHANAKYA Radar

- Mission Control cockpit (CO-SPRINT-103): **Zone 1** left Operational Snapshot · **Zone 2** hero Radar (~60–65%) · **Zone 3** Opportunity Preview **slide-over** (collapsed by default).
- AI Deal Health / operational quadrants — **not** a lender-stage workflow board.
- Four quadrants: **On Track** (N) · **Follow-up Required** (E) · **At Risk** (S) · **Needs Attention** (W).
- Matrix screen is **retired**. Do not restore Matrix.
- Kanban remains below the cockpit as secondary work queue; cards **never** draggable.
- Radar blip hover = tooltip; **single click** = open Preview drawer; **double click** = Opportunity Workspace.
- KPI click → expand collapsible opportunity list under snapshot (toggle to collapse); Radar stays visible.
- Quadrant labels **outside** the dial; never overlap or touch the visualization; radar resizes dynamically.
- Follow **Enterprise Design & UX Standard v1.0** (`enterprise-screen-ux-standard.mdc`): Radar is the hero; clarity over complexity; scrollable page.
- Follow **Data Integrity & Analytics Standard v1.0** (`data-integrity-analytics-standard.mdc`): metrics from LoanFile SSOT, same-session refresh on data change, documented formulas, no demo-as-truth in production.
- Follow **Enterprise Metric Single Implementation** (`enterprise-metric-single-implementation.mdc`): Health Score, Operational Vector, quadrant logic, and related KPIs live in one shared derive path — never reimplemented in UI or AI.
- **Real-time:** subscribe to `compass:loan-files-updated` (`subscribeLoanFilesUpdated`) so Radar / KPIs / vector / tables recompute immediately on LoanFile changes; keep 60s poll + `storage` as fallback only.
- Follow **Layout Integrity & Content Safety** (`layout-integrity-content-safety.mdc`): no overlaps/clipping; radar labels never touch dial; tooltips must not cover persistent scores/KPIs.
- Prefer Active Workspace / Opportunity Workspace from Kanban cards and Preview actions.
- Never change Operational Vector / health scoring when adjusting layout chrome.
- Never show Rejected / Lost / Cancelled / Withdrawn / Closed lenders on Radar cards.
